            IREN, APLD ComputeCo 2) is backed by an investment-grade tenant —
            Amazon, Amazon Web Services (AWS), Microsoft, Oracle — or is an
            IG-rated bond (Hut 8's
            BBB− 2042s); the 7.1–7.75% band is Google-guaranteed paper where the
            tenant is unrated Fluidstack; and the 9.25% outlier (APLD ComputeCo 1)
            is leased to CoreWeave, itself a levered neocloud. Same coupon axis,
            three different credit structures. The faint grey line only orders the
            named vintages by date — it is a reading aid, not a single-driver
            trend.
